05/04/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Romania and Turkey signed a memorandum of understanding in Istanbul on Friday (April 3rd) regarding Romania's participation in the Black Sea naval operation Harmony. 
The two countries will take part in the exercises, along with Ukraine and Russia. 
Black Sea Harmony is an initiative launched by Turkey in March 2004, aimed at deterring naval threats in the Black Sea and expanding the zone of stability and security in the region. 
(Ziua, Financiarul - 03/04/09)
